{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769716195,"nonce":"/RBex7WVsjABWtOUeg/e42uDciQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mzt6S","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/122","origin":"github"},"title":"Worktree naming scheme lacks repository context causing ambiguity","message":"## Problem\n\nThe current worktree naming scheme only uses the issue number (e.g., `issue-42`, `issue-123`), which creates ambiguity and potential conflicts when working across multiple repositories in the layer structure.\n\n### Current Behavior\n\nWorktrees are named: `layers/worktrees/issue-{NUMBER}/`\n\n**Example**: `layers/worktrees/issue-42/`\n\n### Issues\n\n1. **No repository context** - Issue #42 could be from:\n   - Main workspace repo (`ros2_agent_workspace`)\n   - A package repo in the core layer (`marine_msgs`, `marine_tools`)\n   - A sensor driver repo\n   - Any other package repository\n\n2. **Collision risk** - If an agent works on issue #42 from `marine_msgs` AND another agent works on issue #42 from `sensor_driver`, they would try to use the same worktree path, causing conflicts.\n\n3. **Confusion when listing** - `worktree_list.sh` shows \"issue-42\" but doesn't indicate which repository's issue it is.\n\n### Real-World Scenario\n\nAn agent working on a package-level issue discovered this during testing:\n\n```bash\n# Agent A working on marine_msgs issue #5\n.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --issue 5 --type layer --layer core\n\n# Agent B working on sensor_driver issue #5\n.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --issue 5 --type layer --layer sensors\n# ❌ Error: Worktree already exists!\n```\n\nBoth issues are #5, but from different repositories.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nInclude repository identifier in the worktree name:\n\n**Format**: `issue-{REPO_SLUG}-{NUMBER}`\n\n**Examples**:\n- `issue-workspace-42` (main workspace repo)\n- `issue-marine_msgs-5` (marine_msgs package)\n- `issue-sensor_driver-12` (sensor driver package)\n\n### Implementation Details\n\n1. **Detect source repository**:\n   - When using `gh issue view`, check the repository URL\n   - Extract org/repo slug\n   - For main repo: use \"workspace\" as identifier\n   - For package repos: use package name\n\n2. **Update scripts**:\n   - `worktree_create.sh` - Accept `--repo-slug` parameter\n   - `start_issue_work.sh` - Auto-detect repository from GitHub issue\n   - `worktree_enter.sh` - Support new naming pattern\n   - `worktree_remove.sh` - Support new naming pattern\n   - `worktree_list.sh` - Display repository context\n\n3. **Backwards compatibility**:\n   - Support old naming pattern during transition\n   - Migrate existing worktrees or document manual rename\n\n### Alternative Considered\n\nUse full repo path: `issue-org-repo-number`\n- **Pro**: Fully qualified\n- **Con**: Verbose, especially for sub-repos in layers\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Worktrees are named with repository context\n- [ ] No collisions between same issue numbers from different repos\n- [ ] `worktree_list.sh` clearly shows which repo each worktree is for\n- [ ] Documentation updated with new naming scheme\n- [ ] Migration path for existing worktrees (if any)\n\n---\n\n**🤖 Reported-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`","files":null}]}